April 23, 2008.(People.com.cn) April 23. According to the most recent 2008 Harris Poll, the Bible remains the most popular book among American adults.The researchers said that to have such a concordance of viewpoint in the US regardless of sex, age, education, geographical location, race and age is extremely rare.Still, in the online opinion poll, most Americans concurred that the Bible is their favorite book.The poll also revealed that political ties do not influence people's fondness for books--Republicans, Democrats and independants all feel similarly that the Bible and Gone with the Wind are their two favorite books.(Hu Qin)